Human Activity Recognition Using Smartphones Dataset Code book

ACTIVITY LABELS
1: WALKING 
2: WALKING_UPSTAIRS 
3: WALKING_DOWNSTAIRS 
4: SITTING 
5: STANDING 
6: LAYING

FEATURES
- Prefix:
t: Time domain signals
f: Frequency domain signals obtained by using the Fast Fourier Transform

- Signals
BodyAcc: Body acceleration signal
BodyGyro: Body gyroscope signal
GravityAcc: Gravity acceleration signal

- Jerk signal
Jerk: Jerk signal obtained by time derivation of acceleration and angular velocity

- Magnitude:
Mag: Magnitude of the three-dimensional signals calculated using the Euclidean norm

- Directions:
X: 3-axial signals in the X direction
Y: 3-axial signals in the Y direction
Z: 3-axial signals in the Z direction

- Operation:
mean(): Mean value 
std(): Standard deviation 
mad(): Median absolute deviation 
max(): Largest value in array 
min(): Smallest value in array 
sma(): Signal magnitude area 
energy(): Energy measure. Sum of the squares divided by the number of values. 
iqr(): Interquartile range 
entropy(): Signal entropy 
arCoeff(): Autorregresion coefficients with Burg order equal to 4 
correlation(): correlation coefficient between two signals 
maxInds(): index of the frequency component with largest magnitude 
meanFreq(): Weighted average of the frequency components to obtain a mean frequency 
skewness(): skewness of the frequency domain signal 
kurtosis(): kurtosis of the frequency domain signal 
bandsEnergy(): Energy of a frequency interval within the 64 bins of the FFT of each window.
angle(): Angle between two vectors

UNITS
Acceleration features: g (gravitational acceleration)
Gyroscope features: radians/second

DESCRIPTIVE VARIABLES NAMES USED IN THE SCRIPT
activity_ID: Number assigned to every activity considered in the study according to the activity_labels.txt file
activity_Type: Type of activity considered in the study according to the activity_labels.txt file
feature_ID: Number assigned to every feature considered in the study according to the features.txt file
feature_Type: Type of feature considered in the study according to the features.txt file
subject_ID: Number assigned to every participant in the study according to the subject_test.txt file
activity_ID: Type of activity considered in the study according to the y_train.txt file
